An index is a database object that helps MySQL find rows faster
-> Without an index, MySQL may have to scan the entire table row by row
-> With an index, MySQL can locate matching rows much faster

=> An index is a special lookup structure that improves the speed of data retrieval

CREATE INDEX index_name
ON table_name(column_name); -- Create Index

CREATE INDEX idx_rent
ON properties(rent);

Think about a book:
- Without an index, to find 'Window Functions' you may scan every page
- With a book index, you directly jump to the page number
MySQL indexes work the same way

