Which index should SPARK use?
It depends on query patterns, data size, and filtering conditions
Composite indexes are useful for multi-column filters, and indexes should be created on frequently used WHERE, JOIN, and ORDER BY columns

CREATE INDEX idx_column_name ON table_name (column_name);
CREATE INDEX idx_composite ON table_name (column1, column2); -- where several columns are involved
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_unique_column_name ON table_name (column_name); -- Unique index
CREATE FULLTEXT INDEX idx_fulltext_column_name ON table_name (text_column_name); --  support of a full-text search
DROP INDEX idx_column_name ON table_name;
SHOW INDEX FROM table_name;
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM table_name WHERE column_name = 'value';
OPTIMIZE TABLE table_name;

Example 2: Index on rent
