Create indexes on columns that are frequently used in:
- WHERE
- JOIN
- ORDER BY
- GROUP BY

Avoid indexing columns that:
- change very frequently
- have very few unique values in some cases
- are rarely queried 
- belong to very small tables

Example:
If a table has only 20 rows, index benefit may be very small

